### POST /v1/chat/completions - Web Search

Source: https://platform.openai.com/docs/guides/tools-web-search_api-mode=chat

Create a chat completion request with web search enabled. The model will retrieve information from the web before generating a response. Supported models include gpt-4o-search-preview, gpt-4o-mini-search-preview, and gpt-5-search-api.

```APIDOC
## POST /v1/chat/completions

### Description
Create a chat completion with web search enabled. The model retrieves current information from the web before responding to queries.

### Method
POST

### Endpoint
https://api.openai.com/v1/chat/completions

### Parameters

#### Request Body
- **model** (string) - Required - One of: `gpt-4o-search-preview`, `gpt-4o-mini-search-preview`, or `gpt-5-search-api`
- **web_search_options** (object) - Required - Configuration object for web search (can be empty {})
- **messages** (array) - Required - Array of message objects with role and content
  - **role** (string) - Required - Role of the message sender (e.g., "user", "assistant")
  - **content** (string) - Required - Content of the message

### Request Example
